1.Definition and Importance of Version Control Systems (VCS)

Q. Explain what a VCS is.
Ans. VCS is a tool that helps in keeping record of changes made to a file.

Q.Discuss why VCS is essential in software development.
Ans.Tracking Changes.
    Branching and Merging.
    Code Reviews.
    Documentation.

2.Introduction to Git

Q.Describe what Git is and its main features.
Ams.Git is a distributed version control system used for tracking changes in source code during software development.
    Main features:
    Distributed Architecture.
    Branching and Merging.
    Performance.

Q.Compare Git with other version control systems (e.g., Subversion, Mercurial).
Ans.                      Git               Subversion   Mercurial
    Architecture          DVCS              CVCS         DVCS
    Performance           faster            Slower       faster 
    Branching             straightforward   cumbersome   simpler 
    Community             Large             Smaller      Smaller
